Senior police officers will meet in Nairobi on Wednesday to discuss security during this electioneering period.The city's top officers and more than220 regional and county commanders will attend.The meeting will be chaired by Inspector General JosephBoinnet.Early in May, Boinnet doubled the number of police officers who will man the August polls to 180,000, from 95,000 in 2013.The security chiefs held their last such meeting in December.The IEBC has announced that official campaigns will begin on May 28.Read: Uhuru to meet senior police officers in Nairobi on security